What is Blue Green Deployment?
Blue Green Deployment  is a zero-downtime deployment strategy used in production systems to release new version safely
 
Its heavily used in systems running on platforms like kubernetes and CI/CD pipeline 

Core idea: 
You maintain two identical environment
BLUE: Current Live version (deployment)
GREEN: New version (updated app)

At any time only one environment servers real user traffic

How it works: 

1.Current system is Live (Blue)
----------------------------------
*User are using the blue 
*Everything is stable

Users → 🔵 Blue (v1)

2.Deploy to the new version (Green)
-----------------------------------
*You deploy new code to Green 
*But user are NOT using it yet

Users → 🔵 Blue (v1)
          🟢 Green (v2 ready)


3.Test the Green environment
*Run tests  on Green environment
*Check API's , performance,logs

4.Switch traffic
----------------------------------
YOu change routing: 
Before:
Users → 🔵 Blue

After:
Users → 🟢 Green

Now the 🟢 Green will become the production 

5.Blue become the backup 
-----------------------------------
If something breaks 
  Instantly swith back to blue


Advantages: 
*Zero downtime
*Instant rollback
*Safe testing in real environment


